<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-5">Faith services</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Prayer area <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">On-site chapel <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContenta53c17d0f3344f0aacd24d7a481fd859">
</div>
<p>The Trust has a Spiritual Care Team which exists to help and support patients’ own spiritual beliefs and religious practice during a stay in hospital.The hospital chaplain is available 24 hours a day and nursing staff can contact the chaplain on behalf of a patient.  Members of the Spiritual Care Team are also pleased to offer a confidential listening service, and to talk or pray with patients. They will also arrange spiritual, pastoral and religious care appropriate to an individual patient’s needs. If a patient would like to attend one of the regular chapel services, they should let ward staff know.At Gloucestershire Royal Hospital there is a Chapel off the Main Conco</p>
</div>
